from weasyprint import HTML

# Define the HTML content for the Presentation Slides
# We use CSS to force each section onto a new page with a landscape aspect ratio
html_content = """
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <style>
        @page {
            size: 297mm 210mm; /* Landscape A4 */
            margin: 0;
        }
        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Arial, sans-serif;
            color: #2c3e50;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }
        .slide {
            width: 297mm;
            height: 210mm;
            padding: 40px 60px;
            box-sizing: border-box;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            page-break-after: always;
            position: relative;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fdfdfd 0%, #f0f4f8 100%);
        }
        .title-slide {
            background-color: #1a3a5f;
            color: white;
            justify-content: center;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .title-slide h1 {
            font-size: 48pt;
            margin: 0;
            text-transform: uppercase;
        }
        .title-slide h2 {
            font-size: 24pt;
            opacity: 0.9;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }
        .slide-header {
            border-bottom: 3px solid #1a3a5f;
            margin-bottom: 30px;
        }
        .slide-header h2 {
            font-size: 32pt;
            color: #1a3a5f;
            margin: 0;
            padding-bottom: 10px;
        }
        .content {
            flex-grow: 1;
            font-size: 18pt;
        }
        .content ul {
            list-style-type: square;
        }
        .content li {
            margin-bottom: 15px;
        }
        .highlight {
            color: #2980b9;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .footer {
            position: absolute;
            bottom: 20px;
            left: 60px;
            right: 60px;
            font-size: 12pt;
            color: #7f8c8d;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
            padding-top: 10px;
        }
        .two-column {
            display: flex;
            gap: 40px;
        }
        .column {
            flex: 1;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="slide title-slide">
        <h1>NewsBot Intelligence System 2.0</h1>
        <h2>Advanced NLP Integration & Analysis Platform</h2>
        <p style="margin-top: 40px; font-size: 18pt;">Presented by: <strong>Brandon Matias</strong></p>
        <p style="font-size: 14pt;">Houston City College | AI & Robotics | ITAI 2373</p>
    </div>

    <div class="slide">
        <div class="slide-header"><h2>Project Vision & Scope</h2></div>
        <div class="content">
            <p>Moving from the Midterm prototype to a <span class="highlight">Production-Ready AI Platform</span>.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Sophisticated Analysis:</strong> Transition from simple keyword matching to deep semantic understanding.</li>
                <li><strong>Global Connectivity:</strong> Breaking language barriers via automated multilingual workflows.</li>
                <li><strong>User-Centric Design:</strong> Interactive dashboards and conversational interfaces for non-technical stakeholders.</li>
                <li><strong>2026 Readiness:</strong> Optimized for modern binaries (NumPy 2.0) and scalable architecture.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="footer"><span>NewsBot 2.0</span><span>Slide 2</span></div>
    </div>

    <div class="slide">
        <div class="slide-header"><h2>Four Integrated Modules</h2></div>
        <div class="content">
            <div class="two-column">
                <div class="column">
                    <p class="highlight">Module A: Content Analysis</p>
                    <p style="font-size: 14pt;">LDA/NMF Topic Modeling, Sentiment Evolution, and Entity Mapping.</p>
                    
                    <p class="highlight">Module B: Language Understanding</p>
                    <p style="font-size: 14pt;">Intelligent Summarization, Semantic Search, and Contextual Enhancement.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="column">
                    <p class="highlight">Module C: Multilingual Intelligence</p>
                    <p style="font-size: 14pt;">Language Detection, Seamless Translation, and Cross-Lingual Analysis.</p>
                    
                    <p class="highlight">Module D: Conversational Interface</p>
                    <p style="font-size: 14pt;">Natural Language Query Processing and Intent Classification.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="footer"><span>NewsBot 2.0</span><span>Slide 3</span></div>
    </div>

    <div class="slide">
        <div class="slide-header"><h2>Overcoming Engineering Hurdles</h2></div>
        <div class="content">
            <ul>
                <li><strong>NumPy 2.0 Binary Crisis:</strong> Engineered a compatibility bridge for legacy NLP models to run on the 2026 Python ecosystem.</li>
                <li><strong>API Dependency Wrapper:</strong> Developed a custom 'googletrans' replacement using <i>deep-translator</i> to bypass library version locks.</li>
                <li><strong>Sentiment Calibration:</strong> Tightened thresholds to &pm; 0.05 to capture tone in objective journalistic text.</li>
                <li><strong>Scalable Deployment:</strong> Native support for Docker and Heroku cloud environments.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="footer"><span>NewsBot 2.0</span><span>Slide 4</span></div>
    </div>

    <div class="slide">
        <div class="slide-header"><h2>Driving Business Value</h2></div>
        <div class="content">
            <p>Automating the cognitive load of high-volume monitoring.</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>80% Time Reduction:</strong> From hours of manual synthesis to <span class="highlight">Instant Insights</span>.</li>
                <li><strong>Increased Scale:</strong> Capable of monitoring 500+ global sources simultaneously.</li>
                <li><strong>Risk Mitigation:</strong> Real-time detection of negative sentiment breakouts and cultural bias.</li>
                <li><strong>Quantified Savings:</strong> Estimated <strong>$45k+ labor savings</strong> per automated analyst role.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="footer"><span>NewsBot 2.0</span><span>Slide 5</span></div>
